                    .case-study__intro-text-wrapper
                        %p.case-study__introduction
                            Dr. Harvey's was founded in 1980 by Dr. Harvey Cohen, a holistic nutritionist and lifelong animal lover. He created the company to offer all-natural, human-grade pet food without preservatives or artificial additives, which was groundbreaking at the time.
                        %p.case-study__introduction
                            More than 40 years later, Dr. Harvey's remains a family-owned business that provides holistic pet products focused on real, whole-food ingredients, nutrient-rich formulas, and transparent sourcing. The company is dedicated to helping pet owners make informed choices for their pets' health and wellbeing.
                        %p.case-study__introduction
                            To stay competitive in the growing holistic pet food market, the website was modernized to improve usability and visual appeal while keeping the handmade feel that reflects the brand's values. The project focused on increasing conversions with transparency and trust, avoiding aggressive sales tactics, and creating a welcoming, authentic experience for pet owners who value natural and honest products.
                        %p.case-study__introduction
                            %em
                                %strong Notes:
                                Most copywriting and visual assets (graphics and illustrations) were handled by the client's graphic design and marketing teams. I also collaborated with a full-stack developer to implement and refine several front-end features. The research shown here is my own and was not commissioned. The designs represent the original pitch. Some were implemented, others were not.
        .case-study__short-introduction
            .container
                .columns.is-variable.is-6-desktop
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow Snapshot
                        %h2 Overview
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1-desktop
                        .insight__wrapper
                            %p.insights-header
                                Problem
                            %p This audience have high standards and low tolerance for anything that feels generic or salesy. They want enough information to feel confident but not so much that the page feels overwhelming. Trust has to be built visually, not just through copy, and since most of them are landing from social on mobile, the experience needs to hold up on a small screen. The challenge is making a handcrafted, ingredient-driven brand feel premium online without losing the warmth that makes it feel different.
                            %hr
                        .insight__wrapper
                            %p.insights-header
                                Constraints
                            %p We had to work within an existing style guide, so this wasn't a from-scratch brand exercise. Working with a small internal team, every decision also had to be realistic to actually build. Compliance tied to our certifications meant certain claims or language were off the table, and the brand voice always had to feel transparent and natural, never sales-y or pushy. Our customers also weren't especially tech savvy, so everything had to be obvious and self-explanatory, otherwise we'd see conversions drop or people struggle to understand how to use a feature.
                            %hr
                        .insight__wrapper
                            %p.insights-header
                                Solution
                            %p The solution focused on making information and interactions as clear and accessible as possible, without ever feeling like a hard sell. We made next steps obvious, from explicit CTAs to visible carousel buttons once we realized customers didn't know they could scroll manually. Information customers first looked at, like ingredients, product duration, and prep instructions, was surfaced so they didn't have to dig for it. We also refined the food-matching quiz to reduce decision fatigue, and built a free trial page detailing every food so customers could explore and choose with confidence. Visually, we kept the experience feeling handmade, staying true to the brand's natural, transparent tone. Upsells were personalized to complement what a customer already bought or was considering, so they read as helpful guidance rather than a sales push.
                            %hr
                        .insight__wrapper
                            %p.insights-header
                                Impact
                            %ul
                                %li
                                    %span Increased upsells
                                    through personalized recommendations that felt like guidance, not a sales pitch
                                %li
                                    %span Grew autoship signups,
                                    showing customers trusted the recommendations enough to commit long term
                                %li
                                    %span Boosted free trial signups,
                                    giving more people a low-risk way to try the food before buying in
                                %li
                                    %span  Improved SEO and launched a blog,
                                    driving more organic traffic and new customers discovering the brand
        .case-study__background
            .container
                .columns.is-variable.is-6-desktop
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow Discovery
                        %h2 Research
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1-desktop
                        .research__wrapper
                            .subheader
                                Industry Insights
                            %h3 Holistic Pet Food
                            .columns.is-variable.is-2
                                .column
                                    .bubble__wrapper.pink
                                        .bubble__number{ data: { count: 57, prefix: "$", suffix: "B" } }$0B
                                        %p.bubble__text
                                            projected global organic and natural pet food market by 2033, up 82% from 2024
                                        .bubble__source
                                            IMARC Group
                                .column
                                    .bubble__wrapper.blue
                                        .bubble__number{ data: { count: 68, suffix: "%" } } 0%
                                        %p.bubble__text
                                            of US consumers say ingredient transparency is very important when choosing pet food
                                        .bubble__source
                                            PETS International
                                .column
                                    .bubble__wrapper.green
                                        .bubble__number{ data: { count: 40, suffix: "%" } } 0%
                                        %p.bubble__text
                                            of pet food purchases in the US are already made online
                                        .bubble__source
                                            Packaged Facts
                            %p The holistic pet food market is growing fast, and so are customer expectations. Buyers are more informed, more values-driven, and more likely to scrutinize ingredients before they ever add something to cart. With nearly 40% of purchases happening online, the website isn't just a storefront, it's often the deciding factor. That meant our job wasn't to convince people holistic food was worth it, most already believed that. It was to build a site that could earn trust quickly, cut through decision fatigue with too many product types to choose from, and make transparency and confidence part of the actual experience.
                        %hr
                        .research__wrapper
                            .subheader
                                Competitive Audit
                            %h3 Where Dr. Harvey's Stands
                            %p Four competitors were audited across design quality, ingredient transparency, educational content, product discovery, and handcrafted feel. The pattern was consistent: ingredient transparency and educational content have become baseline expectations, largely set by direct competitors that Dr. Harvey's now has to match while retailers raise the bar on product discovery alone.
                            %ul
                                %li
                                    %span Ingredient transparency and educational content
                                    have become the baseline expectation in this category. Competitors leading with ingredients, sourcing, and content set the floor Dr. Harvey's needs to meet.
                                %li
                                    %span Retailers win on discovery but can't offer relationship.
                                    Story, community, and trust are advantages only a brand site can deliver.
                                %li
                                    %span Scale often comes at the cost of authenticity.
                                    The brands that grew biggest lost the handcrafted feel that holistic buyers respond to, making Dr. Harvey's independence a real edge if the site communicates it clearly.
                        %hr
                        .research__wrapper
                            .subheader
                                Users
                            %h3 Understanding Users
                            %p Dr. Harvey's target audience is health-conscious pet owners who treat their animals as an extension of their own wellness lifestyle. The core buyer is a Millennial or Gen Z pet parent, aged 18–38. They're skeptical of conventional options, willing to pay a premium for clean-label, human-grade ingredients, and quick to do their research before buying. Higher-income households round out the audience, drawn in by the brand's transparency and premium positioning. What ties everyone together is a distrust of processed food, a demand for clean labels, and a genuine belief that better nutrition means a healthier, longer life for their pet.
        .case-study__features
            .anchor#features
            .container
                .columns
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow Features
                        %h2 Transforming needs into features
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1
                        %p
                            Based on the user needs identified during the empathizing phase, we decided to focus on a few key features to enhance customer's experience.
                .columns.is-multiline.is-variable.is-3-desktop
                    .column.is-3-desktop.is-6-tablet
                        .case-study-feature.pink
                            %h4.pink Pet profile quiz
                            %h3 A guided entry point for first-time buyers
                            %p An interactive quiz matching a dog's age, size, and dietary needs to the most suitable products. Reduces overwhelm and replaces a complex product range with a clear, personalized starting point.
                    .column.is-3-desktop.is-6-tablet
                        .case-study-feature.green
                            %h4.green Product detail page
                            %h3 Ingredients and preparation front and center
                            %p Ingredient lists, feeding guides, and vet guidance visible before reviews. Directly addresses the most common reason customers leave before purchasing — not knowing how to prepare the food.
                    .column.is-3-desktop.is-6-tablet
                        .case-study-feature.yellow 
                            %h4.yellow Feeding Guides & Blog
                            %h3 Build confidence and show up in search
                            %p Educational content covering holistic nutrition, preparation instructions, ingredient benefits, and transition guidance. Keeps first-time buyers on site instead of sending them elsewhere, and positions Dr. Harvey's as an authority in searches buyers are already making.
                    .column.is-3-desktop.is-6-tablet
                        .case-study-feature.blue 
                            %h4.blue Autoship & Subscriptions
                            %h3 Make it easy to stay a customer
                            %p Subscription and autoship options on all product pages with a clear savings callout. Directly addresses the biggest friction point for repeat buyers and reduces the chance a loyal customer drifts to a retailer for convenience.
